                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12733.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saltillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-03T18:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At a second preliminary conference this afternoon the envoys submitted six
                    conditions from the Government at Mexico City and also said that they were not
                    authorized to make unconditional surrender. In consequence the hope of any
                    settlement here has completely disappeared and the campaign will most actively
                    continue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
